DUBAI: A Saudi businessman has bid SR3 million ($800,000) for a “golden ticket” to the Riyadh Season Cup, a friendly match this month between Lionel Messi’s Paris Saint-Germain and a team made up of players from Saudi sides Al-Nassr, Cristiano Ronaldo’s new club, and Al-Hilal. For the latest updates, follow us on Twitter @ArabNewsSport His bid came after General Entertainment Authority Chairman Turki Al-Sheikh posted a message on Twitter announcing that that the current highest bid for the “Beyond Imagination” ticket was SR2.5 million, made by businessman Abdulaziz Baghlef, and asking “Where are the bidders?” In response, Baghlef immediately increased his bid to SR3 million and said on Twitter: “I am honored to raise the fee to SR3m … thank you, your excellency, for this distinguished charitable initiative of Ehsan Charity Platform.” Along with his tweet, Al-Sheikh included a video that gives details of what the winning bidder for the Beyond Imagination ticket will get for their money. The 79-second clip had been viewed more than 3.6 million times as of midnight on Tuesday. The ticket holder will attend the presentation ceremony after the game with Al-Sheikh, meet star players including Messi, Ronaldo, Kylian Mbappe and Neymar, and line up alongside the winning side in their official team photo. They will also attend a gala lunch and visit the dressing rooms of both teams at the King Fahd Stadium in Riyadh, where the game will be played. French champions PSG announced on Monday that Messi will play in the friendly against a select side of players from Al-Nassr and Saudi rivals Al-Hilal on Jan. 19. The auction for the Beyond Imagination ticket began on Jan. 9 with an opening price of SR1 million and bidding will remain open until 11:30 p.m. local time on Jan. 17. All the proceeds will be donated to the National Platform for Charitable Work, also known as Ehsan.